{
  "id": "piston-door-3x3",
  "title": "3x3 Piston Door",
  "category": "door",
  "description": "A 3x3 flush door using double piston extenders so the corner blocks can clear a 3-wide opening. Each of the four corners is driven by a double extender (a sticky piston pushing another sticky piston) so the corner block travels two spaces out of the doorway; the center edges use single sticky pistons. All extenders must fire in the correct order, so the control circuit chains observers or repeater delays: the outer (rear) pistons fire first, the inner (front) pistons a tick later. A lever or button on each side feeds a shared redstone line behind the wall. This is an advanced build \u2014 keep the two sides mirrored and give yourself at least 2 blocks of wall depth for the extender mechanism.",
  "aliases": [
    "3x3 door",
    "big piston door",
    "jeb door",
    "vault door"
  ],
  "inputs": [
    "lever"
  ],
  "outputs": [],
  "footprint": "3x10x7",
